## Claude SubagentDetector System - Comprehensive Exploration Report

### Overview

The Claude SubagentDetector is an event-driven system that automatically detects, monitors, and manages Claude Code subagent sessions spawned during a main session. It integrates directory watching, JSONL event parsing, and optional pane auto-opening for tmux environments.

---

## 1. Core Architecture

### 1.1 Shared Interfaces (`src/core/detector-interfaces.ts`)

```typescript
// OutputHandler: Abstract output mechanism
interface OutputHandler {
  info(message: string): void;
  warn(message: string): void;
  error(message: string): void;
  debug(message: string): void;
}

// SessionHandler: Interactive mode session management (optional)
interface SessionHandler {
  addSession?(agentId: string, label: string, path: string): void;
  markSessionDone?(agentId: string): void;
