## 8. Key Mechanisms

### 8.1 Early vs. Fallback Detection

| Mechanism | Trigger | When | Agentid Known? | Pane Opens? |
|-----------|---------|------|---|---|
| **Early** | Task tool_use | Before spawn | No | Yes (async) |
| **Fallback** | toolUseResult | After complete | Maybe | No (completed) |
| **Resume** | agent_progress | Re-entry | Yes (must be) | Yes |

### 8.2 Description Queue (FIFO)

- **Queue**: `pendingDescriptions: string[]`
- **Push**: When Task tool_use with description detected (parseAssistantMessage)
- **Consume**: 
  - `registerNewAgent()`: Shift and pass to `onNewSubagent` (pane naming)
  - `handleFallbackDetection()`: Shift even if no pane (prevent drift)
- **Clear**: On `detector.stop()` (prevent timer leaks)

### 8.3 Parser Statelessness (Multi-Session)

- ClaudeLineParser is **stateful** (currentMessageState, lastProcessedLine)
- Each session label gets **independent parser instance**
- On switch: New Map of parsers created (old instances GC'd)
- **Why**: Prevents message skip bugs when switching between sessions

### 8.4 Output Filtering (--pane mode)

```typescript
const suppressedForPane = new Set(existingAgentIds);  // Pre-existing agents

const shouldOutput = (label) => {
  if (label === MAIN_LABEL) return true;              // Always show main
  const agentId = extractAgentIdFromLabel(label);
  if (suppressedForPane.has(agentId)) return false;  // Hide if in set
  return !pm.hasPaneForAgent(agentId);               // Hide if pane open
};
```

- **Pre-existing suppressed**: History not shown (pane opens later)
- **New agents suppressed**: History not shown (pane opens via onNewSubagent)
- **Release on pane close**: Still suppressed (already output to pane)

### 8.5 Super-Follow (Auto-Switch)

- **Polling**: Every 500ms via `createSuperFollowController`
- **Delay**: 5s debounce before switch (avoid rapid flipping)
- **Scope**: Project directory (not hardcoded)
- **Activity time**: Considers subagent mtimes (latest activity wins)
- **Title reading**: On-demand only (perf: skip during polling)

