### 1. **Core Components Overview**

#### **SessionManager** (`src/core/session-manager.ts`)
Manages multiple watcher sessions for interactive switching. Key interface:

```typescript
export interface WatcherSession {
  id: string;                    // 'main' or agentId
  label: string;                 // '[MAIN]' or '[a0627b6]'
  path: string;                  // File path
  buffer: string[];              // Output buffer (history)
  isDone: boolean;               // Completion flag
  createdAt: number;             // Timestamp
  displayName?: string;          // Custom title (Claude only)
}

export class SessionManager {
  addSession(id, label, path, displayName?): WatcherSession
  getAllSessions(): WatcherSession[]
  getActiveSession(): WatcherSession | null
  switchNext(): WatcherSession | null
  switchPrev(): WatcherSession | null
  switchTo(id): WatcherSession | null
  handleOutput(label, content): void         // Buffers all, displays active
  flushActiveBuffer(): void                  // Show buffered history
  updateSessionDisplayName(id, displayName): void
  markSessionDone(id): void
  getWatchedFiles(): WatchedFile[]
}
```

Key logic: `handleOutput()` buffers all sessions but **only displays active session**. On switch, `flushActiveBuffer()` replays buffered history.

#### **DisplayController** (`src/interactive/display-controller.ts`)
Terminal UI: persistent status line at bottom, content area above.

```typescript
export class DisplayController {
  init(): void                           // Setup scroll region + status line
  destroy(): void                        // Restore terminal state
  write(content): void                   // Output to content area
  updateStatusLine(sessions, activeIndex): void
  showSwitchMessage(session, historyContent): void
}
```

Status line format: `[3/20] MAIN(50) | [a0627b6](12) | [b1f23c9] (Tab/q)` where `(N)` = buffer size.

